  <section cache:ref-path="08|02|12|.04">
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.04</num>
    <heading>Prohibitions.</heading>
    <para>
      <num>A.</num>
      <text>Except as authorized by <cite doc="Md. Code" path="gnr|4-2">Natural Resources Article, §4-2</cite>A-08(a), Annotated Code of Maryland, or by a permit issued by the Secretary under <cite path="08|02|12|.04|B.">§B of this regulation</cite>, a person may not take, possess, transport, export, process, sell, offer for sale, deliver, carry, or ship any fish of the species listed in Regulation .03A and B of this chapter.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>B.</num>
      <text>Permit to Take or Possess Endangered or Threatened Species.</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>The Secretary may issue a permit, under the terms and conditions he prescribes, to allow the taking or possession of species listed in Regulation.03A and B of this chapter for:</text>
        <para>
          <num>(a)</num>
          <text>Scientific purposes;</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <num>(b)</num>
          <text>Enhancing the propagation and survival of a species; or</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <num>(c)</num>
          <text>Aquaculture purposes in accordance with <cite path="|08.02.14">COMAR 08.02.14</cite>.</text>
        </para>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Violation of any provision or restriction of the permit shall constitute a violation of this regulation and may result, at the discretion of the Secretary, in revocation of the permit and confiscation of those species held pursuant to it.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>C.</num>
      <text>A person may take, possess, transport, export, process, sell, or offer for sale, or ship those species designated as in need of conservation in <cite path="|08|02|12|.03|E.">Regulation .03E of this chapter</cite> unless prohibited by regulations adopted by the Department for each individual species.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>D.</num>
      <text>Penalty. Violation of any provision of this regulation is subject to all penalties and actions included in Natural Resources Article, §§<cite doc="Md. Code" path="gnr|4-2">4-2</cite>A-<cite doc="Md. Code" path="gnr|07">07</cite> and <cite doc="Md. Code" path="gnr|4-1207">4-1207</cite>, Annotated Code of Maryland. This may result in seizure of the fishing license and ultimate confiscation of all fish, fishing gear, equipment, and vessel used in the fishing activity.</text>
    </para>
